  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Africa Regional: Promoting Gender Equality among Unions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Solidarity Center, through a regional intensive gender training and women&#x2019;s empowerment project, is working to help union organizations achieve gender equality goals through education and campaign assistance.  The program includes testing and revising new educational materials in Zimbabwe for use in either a coordinated campaign or a series of national campaigns.
This project is a small part of Solidarity Center&#x2019;s gender-equality work around the globe, which includes programs to increase union leaders&#x2019; awareness of gender equality issues and to use unions&#x2019; bargaining and advocacy strength to fight gender-based violence and sexual harassment, as well as to address issues such as unfair hiring and promotion practices, unsafe workplaces, low wages and the need for benefits such as maternity/paternity leave and health care.</narrative>
  </description>
